This confirms the issue. There is a mismatch between your SriovNetwork objects and the SriovNetworkNodePolicy objects.

What I found

Your node advertises only these SR-IOV resources:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_1
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2_1

Your pod is requesting:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

There is no such allocatable resource on the node.

At the same time, you have created these SriovNetwork objects:

bscf-bh0u-3-nad
bscf-bh0u-3-1-nad

But your SriovNetworkNodePolicy list contains only:

policy-ens1f0-bh0u
policy-ens3f3-bh0u-1
policy-ens4f0-bh0u-2
policy-ens6f0-bh0u-2-1

There is no:

policy-*-bh0u-3
policy-*-bh0u-3-1

So the SR-IOV device plugin never advertises:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3_1

Therefore the scheduler reports:

Insufficient openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3


---

Verify the SriovNetwork resource names

Run:

oc get sriovnetwork bscf-bh0u-3-nad -n openshift-sriov-network-operator -o yaml

and

oc get sriovnetwork bscf-bh0u-3-1-nad -n openshift-sriov-network-operator -o yaml

Pay particular attention to:

spec:
  resourceName:

If it is:

resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

then the corresponding SriovNetworkNodePolicy must exist with:

spec:
  resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

Currently it does not.


---

Also check your Helm values

Your deployment is requesting:

resources:
  requests:
    openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3: 1

Verify whether this is intentional. If your hardware only has four PF groups (bh0u, bh0u_1, bh0u_2, bh0u_2_1), then the Helm chart may be using the wrong resource name.


---

Another issue you'll hit next

Even after fixing the SR-IOV resource, your node currently has:

16 GiB / 18 GiB hugepages already allocated.

Your pending pod requires 8 GiB hugepages.


So after fixing bh0u_3, you'll still need to either:

free hugepages by stopping other pods,

increase hugepages on the node, or

reduce the pod's hugepage request.


My conclusion

The scheduler error is valid. Your deployment references openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3, but the node does not advertise that resource because there is no matching SriovNetworkNodePolicy for bh0u_3.

One question: Is this BSCF Helm chart provided by Samsung, or did you create the SR-IOV policies yourself? That will determine whether the fix is to correct the Helm values or to create the missing SriovNetworkNodePolicy for bh0u_3.
